sections.faq:
How often should I apply it?
Apply Mosquito Deleto every 14 days in regions with higher precipitation, or every 28 days for drier areas. Apply Nix Ticks after rainfall or as needed.
Should I spray my entire lawn?
Rather than covering the entire lawn, designate a “protected zone” in the area where you spend the most time. Spray this zone regularly.
How do I apply it?
Spray in an up and down motion, working quickly to cover your protected lawn area, trees, mulch, and bushes until all foliage is just fully wet.
How many square feet does one bottle cover?
Up to 5,000 sq. ft.
Should I use these products before or after Sunday nutrients?
You can apply either one first—the order is totally up to you! Regardless, you’ll want to wait 24 hours between those applications to avoid washing out or diluting either formula.
What's the difference between Mosquito Deleto and Nix Ticks?
Mosquito Deleto and Nix Ticks contain cedar in different concentrations which is an effective bug killer and repellent, killing both pests and larvae on contact. Nix Ticks has a higher concentration of Cedar Oil to target ticks more strongly. And Mosquito Deleto contains lemongrass oil in addition to the cedar oil which is effective at repelling mosquitoes.
Are there any US states or territories where Mosquito Deleto is not approved for use?
Mosquito Deleto is not yet approved for use in the following states and territories: AS, DC, GU, ID, IN, MD, ME, MP, MS, MT, PR, SD, VI.
Are there any US states or territories where Nix Ticks is not approved for use?
Nix Ticks is not yet approved for use in the following states and territories: DC, ID, IN, MD, ME, MS, MT.
